IMPORTANT CONSIDERATIONS AND DISCLAIMER:
•	LEGAL ADVICE IS CRUCIAL: THIS SAMPLE IS FOR INFORMATIONAL PURPOSES ONLY AND DOES NOT CONSTITUTE LEGAL ADVICE. CHORD PROGRESSIONS CAN BE COMPLEX IN TERMS OF COPYRIGHTABILITY, ESPECIALLY GIVEN THE COMMONALITY OF CERTAIN SEQUENCES. A LAWYER SPECIALIZING IN INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY AND ENTERTAINMENT LAW SHOULD BE CONSULTED TO DRAFT OR REVIEW ANY ACTUAL AGREEMENT.
•	JURISDICTION: LAWS VARY SIGNIFICANTLY BY COUNTRY AND REGION. THE "GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION" SECTION IS CRITICAL AND MUST BE TAILORED TO THE SPECIFIC CONTEXT.
•	SPECIFICS OF THE CHORD PROGRESSION: THE MORE UNIQUE AND DEVELOPED A CHORD PROGRESSION, THE STRONGER ITS POTENTIAL FOR COPYRIGHT PROTECTION. AGREEMENTS SHOULD IDEALLY REFERENCE A SPECIFIC, IDENTIFIABLE PROGRESSION (E.G., BY MUSICAL NOTATION OR AUDIO FILE).
•	CLARITY IS KEY: AMBIGUITY CAN LEAD TO DISPUTES. ENSURE ALL TERMS, ESPECIALLY REGARDING RIGHTS, COMPENSATION, AND TERMINATION, ARE CRYSTAL CLEAR IN THE INDIVIDUAL AGREEMENT.
•	REGISTRATION: CONSIDER WHETHER REGISTERING THE UNDERLYING MUSICAL WORK (IF APPLICABLE) THAT CONTAINS THE CHORD PROGRESSION IS BENEFICIAL FOR PROTECTION.

